Chappell's work for NPR includes being the lead writer for online coverage of several Olympic Games, from London in 2012 and Rio in 2016 to Pyeongchang in 2018 – stints that also included posting numerous videos and photos to NPR's Instagram and other branded accounts. He has also previously been NPR.org's homepage editor. Chappell established the Peabody Award-winning StoryCorps on NPR's website; his assignments also include being the lead web producer for NPR's trip to Asia's Grand Trunk Road. Chappell has coordinated special digital features for Morning Edition and Fresh Air, in addition to editing the rundown of All Things Considered. He also frequently contributes to other NPR blogs, such as The Salt. At NPR, Chappell has trained both digital and radio staff to tell compelling stories, promoting more collaboration between departments and desks. Chappell was a key editorial member of the small team that performed one of NPR's largest website redesigns. One year later, NPR.org won its first Peabody Award, along with the National Press Foundation's Excellence in Online Journalism award. Prior to joining NPR, Chappell was part of the Assignment Desk at CNN International, working with reporters in areas from the Middle East, Asia, Africa, Europe, and Latin America. Chappell also edited and produced stories for CNN.com's features division, before moving on to edit video and produce stories for Sports Illustrated's website. Early in his career, Chappell wrote about movies, restaurants, and music for alternative weeklies, in addition to his first job: editing the police blotter."}]

Your Ultimate Music Destination! At KESM, we\'re all about the music! From 5:30 until Midnight we\'re your go-to source for the finest in Country music. Tune in for a blend of your favorite Top 40 hits, the latest releases, and some cherished country classics you may not have heard in a while. Fridays are a special treat, featuring Oldies rock and roll chart-toppers from the 50s, 60s, 70s, and a dash of the 80s. Don\'t miss our soul-stirring Bluegrass Music show every Sunday from 11 AM to 12 PM, where tradition and innovation harmonize in a musical journey you won\'t want to miss. Here at KESM, expect the unexpected! With our eclectic mix, you never know what you\'re going to hear next. Explore our website for more - from the Birthday Bash to our dedicated Personalities, Programs and Shows, and local news updates at 6:30 AM, 7:30 AM, noon, and 5:00 PM. Serving the Tri-County area, we\'re proud to cover Cedar, St. Clair, Vernon, and portions of Barton, Bates, Benton, Dade, Henry, Hickory, and Polk counties. Experience the rhythm of your community with KESM on 105.5 FM!" "Meet the KESM Team Our KESM FM team is a group of dedicated and skilled individuals who work tirelessly behind the scenes to bring you the best in radio entertainment. With a shared passion for music and a commitment to our community, our team members play integral roles in making KESM FM a beloved radio station. While their specific tasks may vary, they all share a common goal - to provide you with quality programming and a memorable listening experience. Together, we make the magic happen at KESM FM!" "At KESM FM, our music selection is a harmonious blend of timeless classics, current chart-toppers, and hidden gems from a variety of genres. Whether you\'re a fan of Top 40 country hits, beloved country classics, or the soul-stirring sounds of Bluegrass, we\'ve got your musical tastes covered. And remember each Friday we give a taste of past with our Oldies Rock and Roll. Our carefully curated playlists ensure that every moment you spend with us is filled with the best music, no matter your preference. Discover the perfect soundtrack for your day at KESM FM."
